When I first saw screenshots and videos of the game, it looked like a clone of a certain 3 lane endless runner but with a Ben 10 skin on it. Now that I have bought the game and played it, I can really say that it is not that. It's not an endless runner, it has levels and stages that advance in difficulty, and enemies and boss battles. The inclusion of the Omnitrix and the aliens is what differs it from other games. The Omnitrix times out like in the show, and while it's recharging you can still use it but it will give you a random alien which is a cool feature that I am really fond of. My only complaint is that there are still glitches and bugs that happen throughout gameplay, such as the revival tokens disappearing for no apparent reason. I really enjoy this game, and there are a few comic pages that explain the origin of where Ben got the Omnitrix, which has not been shown in the show as of January 2017. Great game however I am not too sure if it is worth the price.
